-- Draghi Says Bond Spreads ‘Most Important’ Engine for Reforms
-- B y   S i m o n e   M e i e r
-- 2012-01-27T13:28:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/draghi-says-bond-spreads-most-important-engine-for-reforms.html
European Central Bank President
 Mario Draghi  said bond spreads are the “most potent engine”
for government reforms in the euro region.  “They have to undertake the necessary fiscal
consolidation, it’s unavoidable,” Draghi said at the  World
Economic Forum  in  Switzerland , Davos, today. “There will be a
short-term contraction. We have to rebuild trust among the
countries of the euro area.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Simone Meier at 
 smeier@bloomberg.net  